commit_message:
Hyper-V: Adds VolumeOps unit tests

The Hyper-V driver oldest tests (test_hypervapi.py) are proving hard to
maintain.

The tests in test_hypervapi.py in particular can also be refactored and
split in separate TestCases, one of each *ops module.

This commit refactors the VolumeOps test cases.

Co-Authored-By: Robert Tingirica <rtingirica@cloudbasesolutions.com>

Partially implements: blueprint hyper-v-test-refactoring

Change-Id: I33d11bf29e7e7a29711e374fdce42a1f8b35f247

commit_message:
Skip non-doc and test-only jobs for for all branches

There is no much reason to skip it for master but not feature and
stable branches. And it only makes life harder for those stuck with
their features in feature branches.

This partially reapplies I4954a2aa7b2ede85843ccd51686bf648dd3782c6
which was reverted in I2528ac44830bacdad2f99f2320e896f1b92b691c.

Change-Id: I76baa13cfc60b4066082babca2a3d25773707a3b

commit_message:
Made Functional Test Key 256 Bits

The test_secrets.py module defines a symmetric key. The symmetric key
length is 256 bits, but the corresponding key was not 256 bits long.
This change makes the key 256 bits.

Change-Id: I41c05518f7b0051b6cd093f3cd37deda7034a4e4

commit_message:
fix scheduler job removal when api not available

When using the api service, the scheduler fetches the
list of jobs from the api.
When the api communication fails the jobs were erroneously
removed anymore.
This does not happen anymore

Change-Id: Id5323c68dfc8b9c420a4b3f7b16b618c2f5699ce
Closes-Bug: #1482610

commit_message:
Allow to build fuel-library package without internet access

Define USE_PREDEFINED_FUEL_LIB_PUPPET_MODULES as URL for
downloading prepared sources, before building fuel-library
package.
This hack required for build fuel-library package
in case build-env don't have access to internet and related to
change [1].

[1]. https://review.openstack.org/#/c/211154/

Сloses-bug: #1482667

Change-Id: I02e02ef62bcc65b96fe17806105394302b2a92d1

subject: Removed the non-existent method call
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-08-13 19:52:18.000000000', 'files': ['trove/tests/unittests/taskmanager/test_vertica_clusters.py', 'trove/tests/unittests/cluster/test_cluster_controller.py', 'trove/tests/unittests/cluster/test_cluster_vertica_controller.py', 'trove/tests/unittests/cluster/test_cluster.py', 'trove/tests/unittests/cluster/test_vertica_cluster.py'], 'message': 'Removed the non-existent method call

<mock_object>.<method>.assert_called/<mock_object>.assert_called()
has been called at many places to assert the execution of method.

However, any such method does not exist(discussed in detail in bug).

Replaced <mock_object>.<method>.assert_called/<mock_object>.assert_called()
by <mock_object>.<method>.assert_called_with(*args, **kwargs).

There is one more benefit of using assert_called_with that
we have verified the exact argumens which were used in method call.

After correcting this found more bugs about invalid asserts,
which were working earlier because of mocked method call,
which started failing.
Corrected these bugs, too.

Change-Id: I638e38245676cffdffacb8e4d8316ed18acb1fa3
Closes-Bug: #1469812
(cherry picked from commit 822d2c69abc2f5dc3246fc25e6bcfa8e9d197ae3)
(commit was pared down to only include necessary fixes.)
'}]
commit_message:
Removed the non-existent method call

<mock_object>.<method>.assert_called/<mock_object>.assert_called()
has been called at many places to assert the execution of method.

However, any such method does not exist(discussed in detail in bug).

Replaced <mock_object>.<method>.assert_called/<mock_object>.assert_called()
by <mock_object>.<method>.assert_called_with(*args, **kwargs).

There is one more benefit of using assert_called_with that
we have verified the exact argumens which were used in method call.

After correcting this found more bugs about invalid asserts,
which were working earlier because of mocked method call,
which started failing.
Corrected these bugs, too.

Change-Id: I638e38245676cffdffacb8e4d8316ed18acb1fa3
Closes-Bug: #1469812
(cherry picked from commit 822d2c69abc2f5dc3246fc25e6bcfa8e9d197ae3)
(commit was pared down to only include necessary fixes.)

commit_message:
Fix order of parms in assertEqual for scheduler ut

When assertEqual is used it should be assertEqual(expected, observed).
Constant values are always the expected.  This patch makes them the
first parameter and fixes some other non-constant cases.

Closes-Bug: #1482373
Change-Id: Iec771d35d1005434281f9efd8bed8d53134abc7f

commit_message:
Allow nova key/partition/password injection

This commit adds the following new variables to customise whether nova
will allow key/partition/password injection:

nova_libvirt_inject_key
nova_libvirt_inject_partition
nova_libvirt_inject_password

Additionally, the following variable has been added to allow setting
password via Horizon:

horizon_can_set_password

Lastly, password injection can now be tested with tempest via:

tempest_compute_change_password

Note that all variables have been defaulted to their current values.

Closes-Bug: #1469238

Change-Id: Iff434ed7c042f7990990485c34d0f35b9a7baa7a

commit_message:
Fix commonName for Cobbler SSL certificate

During docker build process, there is no hostname set,
sometimes breaking cobbler container puppet run.
Now the SSL certificate uses a temporary hostname
during build (and is subsequently regenerated
during deploy with the new hostname).

Change-Id: I56cbdbc61be2c638b57beb09872b0412da3c12e8
Closes-Bug: #1484858

commit_message:
Bug #1484523: Make ODL_NETVIRT_DEBUG_LOGS disabled by default

This commit changes the default DEBUG logs to be disabled, and have
it enabled when networking-odl is used as part of devstack gate test.
This is needed so debug logs don't need to be explicitly disabled in
non-test deployments of Opendaylight with Openstack.

Change-Id: I6f3cade7d0b86a4ecc637a5e5847d93a46509ed9

commit_message:
Use magnum specific flavor

As infra uses public cloud to run jenkins jobs, some cloud
provider do not have large disk space, for example, only 20GB
root disk, not fit for k8s bay instance space requirements.
According to infra core said, if two instances are booted,
each with 10GB, it could all meet in back end clouds.
So we need to create specific flavor for magnum use. It is
verified in local env 8GB can work, so we will use 8GB now.

Closes-Bug: #1484772
Change-Id: I159623f77ad7e3083a5296b0ccc7d65cfb57e001

commit_message:
Add libvirt provider for Vagrant

This change provides possibility to use vagrant-libvirt
plugin, whichby default uses KVM hypervisor. NFS is used
here for syncing /vagrant directory.

To run Vagrant with libvirt provider:

vagrant up --provider=libvirt

Change-Id: I90383717de1f04a90bdaa18d6eb1561fb77cc061

commit_message:
Fix keystone provider to work with v3 auth_url

Fuel's current openrc uses v2.0 keystone API, but
the keystone providers use v3. It is necessary to
strip the version string from OS_AUTH_URL in order
for them to function. This was not a bug on hosts
where keystone is on the same host as where the
resources are created because keystone.conf is used.

Summary of changes:
* Added auth_url_version function to openstacklib credentials.rb
* Fetch auth_url from credentials class in keystone base provider
* Added OS_PROJECT_NAME to openrc (for openrc validation in openstacklib)
* Moved auth_file to be evaluated after keystone admin role
* Added openrc purge before evaluating keystone admin role
* Add workaround for missing HOME for finding /root/openrc
* Add spec tests for openstacklib and keystone

Upstream-Change-Id: I63278fbb34d4a2e37861d0ec411226feb27ef9dc
Upstream-Change-Id: I33c932f3dd4bacf95e44d5291e7b3bdb1597974f
Change-Id: Ifd0f378d189424e8fdf65f13a0f95fe8f50d4a45
Closes-Bug: #1479382

commit_message:
solve duplicate declaration issue for python-openstackclient

when having a controller node with several modules that use puppet-openstacklib
the package python-openstackclient is already declared. because openstacklib
adds the tag 'openstack' to the resource, we have to do it here to. otherwise
ensure_resource does not recognize it and we have a duplicate declaration
for the package.

Change-Id: Icf341ea92764f2ddb60b0e7ace09a56febe59545
Closes-Bug: #1483663

commit_message:
Fix node deletion task manager

* if primary controller was deleted there was no reelection, because
  Deployment task filters out node by pending_deletion flag, so we
  should set it to True when delete the node
* it was possible to run deployment in parallel on the same cluster,
  which causes failures, add validation to prevent this

Change-Id: I634c9165195ddafed8a12e305874867fc534ecb0
Closes-bug: #1473529

commit_message:
Revert "Remove version from os_auth_url in service_credentials"

This reverts commit 33f133ab0cd37da5366769603ece67877505e7c9.

Apparently the way keystone info is used in aodh is different from how
ceilometer uses it. With the change to be reverted in place, none of the
agents can talk to services.

Change-Id: I462f7c4977f14e45069e2c826abd7944252bd9d9

subject: Add process monitoring for LBaaS agents
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-08-13 18:03:49.000000000', 'files': ['monasca_setup/detection/plugins/neutron.py'], 'message': 'Add process monitoring for LBaaS agents

Add neutron-lbaas-agent (LBaaS V1) and neutron-lbaasv2-agent (LBaaS
V2) to the neutron detection plugin.  Because the string
"neutron-lbaas-agent" can be both a process name and log file name,
the process monitor is susceptible to false positive matching on that
string. Use a longer part of the python path to disambiguate this

Change-Id: I3081639a6f36a276bab2f9eb1b9b39a5bef452f1
'}]
commit_message:
Add process monitoring for LBaaS agents

Add neutron-lbaas-agent (LBaaS V1) and neutron-lbaasv2-agent (LBaaS
V2) to the neutron detection plugin.  Because the string
"neutron-lbaas-agent" can be both a process name and log file name,
the process monitor is susceptible to false positive matching on that
string. Use a longer part of the python path to disambiguate this

Change-Id: I3081639a6f36a276bab2f9eb1b9b39a5bef452f1

commit_message:
Use neutron-netns-cleanup utility

Utility neutron-netns-cleanup is extended to cover cleaning features
of both OCF and q-agent-cleanup. It is responsible for:
 * terminating in-namespace processes
 * removing net interfaces and OVS ports
 * removing namespaces
New utility uses pyroute2 library and at least 3 times faster than
the old solution.

Closes-Bug: #1436414
Closes-Bug: #1434196

Change-Id: Id8f12e7a342ccad3c3362d70159101bb95d918fd

commit_message:
Add RAIDInterface for RAID configuration

This commit introduces a new standard interface
of a driver - RAIDInterface.  Drivers can
implement this interface to do RAID configuration.

This commit also introduces some common code to
do validation of RAID configuration and updating
the node after doing RAID configuration.

Change-Id: I907447511e6f9ee9e1e3b96a94a0360e81f75cef
Implements: blueprint ironic-generic-raid-interface

Commit c59dfacef8c211b7e114e634ca17f225bde6c3e0 removed the q-vpn

commit_message:
Add q-vpn back to base services but exclude for liberty runs

Commit c59dfacef8c211b7e114e634ca17f225bde6c3e0 removed the q-vpn
service from being enabled in all neutron runs which is OK for liberty
since that project has it's own devstack plugin and job configs for
master, but it breaks stable/kilo.

So add the q-vpn service back in for kilo.

Related-Bug: #1473475

Change-Id: I69ea5b194fec520e1aa31eb0554cf83c447a5e18

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-08-12 17:20:01.000000000', 'files': ['manilaclient/tests/unit/v1/test_shell.py', 'manilaclient/v1/shell.py'], 'message': 'Make spec_driver_handles_share_servers required

This change makes the extra spec "spec_driver_handles_share_servers"
required for the type-create command in the Manila Client as opposed 
to being listed as an optional argument that was in fact required. I
had to remove a no longer valid test case in the unit test suite, 
but it was done because instead of throwing an exception, the 
argparser will just exit(2).

Change-Id: I0dc58cdfe10493a8eb736fa1bd0cd196bb0f5c05
Closes-Bug: #1484156
'}]
commit_message:
Make spec_driver_handles_share_servers required

This change makes the extra spec "spec_driver_handles_share_servers"
required for the type-create command in the Manila Client as opposed 
to being listed as an optional argument that was in fact required. I
had to remove a no longer valid test case in the unit test suite, 
but it was done because instead of throwing an exception, the 
argparser will just exit(2).

Change-Id: I0dc58cdfe10493a8eb736fa1bd0cd196bb0f5c05
Closes-Bug: #1484156

commit_message:
Hyper-V: Adds MigrationOps unit tests

The Hyper-V driver oldest tests (test_hypervapi.py) are proving hard to
maintain.

The tests in test_hypervapi.py in particular can also be refactored and
split in separate TestCases, one of each *ops module.

This commit refactors the MigrationOps test cases.

Co-Authored-By: Robert Tingirica <rtingirica@cloudbasesolutions.com>

Partially implements: blueprint hyper-v-test-refactoring-liberty

Change-Id: I9167cd9878175902a5b3293e9adc69045d1e8540

commit_message:
Add retry logic when delete a NFS share in VNX

Currently, if user try to delete several NFS shares on same VDM,

VNX backend would report: unable to acquire lock(s).

Use 'retry' logic to handle such kind of error.

Change-Id: I0dafbda265daf19de3d71ee91fc51fb62313e5ec
Closes-Bug: 1480856

commit_message:
Use contextlib.nested for multiple 'with' clauses

Multiple form of 'with' clause doesn't allow line break after eacn item.
It prevents pretty formatting of a big statement.

Nova widely uses contextlib.nested function for this purpose.

Change-Id: I928c5033064f08ec255a2818e11d9619afe749bc

commit_message:
basic integration tests for freezer-agent

The test provided in the tests/integration directory
execute the command line version of the freezer-agent.

The tests execute backups and restores, passing the parameters
on the command line, and check the results.

Types of integration tests depend on the environment variables defined.

Local storage tests are enabled by default and use temporary
files and directories, while SSH and Swift storage testing need
also access to existing external resources.

To enable the ssh storage testing, the following environment
variables need to be defined:

 - FREEZER_TEST_SSH_USERNAME
 - FREEZER_TEST_SSH_KEY
 - FREEZER_TEST_SSH_HOST
 - FREEZER_TEST_CONTAINER

To enable the swift storage testing, the following environment
variables need to be defined:

 - FREEZER_TEST_OS_USERNAME
 - FREEZER_TEST_OS_TENANT_NAME
 - FREEZER_TEST_OS_REGION_NAME
 - FREEZER_TEST_OS_PASSWORD
 - FREEZER_TEST_OS_AUTH_URL

Tests involving LVM snapshots are executed only with superuser
privileges and if the following env variable is not defined:

 - FREEZER_TEST_NO_LVM

Change-Id: I39f0c9bf62f7c82f81ad95f19cf0f7aefb059633

commit_message:
Add python-dracclient project under Ironic

The library will be used by the DRAC driver in Ironic. The current
driver code will be refactored and most of it will move to the library.
The reason behind the move is that it has been difficult for
ironic-cores to review vendor specific code and it also requires an
actual hardware to test it.

Depends-On: I60983b269a5cab715183deec7f3c99feac642403
Change-Id: I11a58f047eb99352dbde7f403b11172de82d2e0d

The compute manager's rebuild_instance doesn't detach a volume correctly

commit_message:
rebuild_instance doesn't detach cinder volumes correctly

The compute manager's rebuild_instance doesn't detach a volume correctly
prior to trying to stand up the vm again. rebuild_instance() defines
detach_block_devices to call cinder's detach_volume() API. This doesn't
actually detach anything, rather it just updates the database.

This change adds a call to terminate_connection to correctly detach the
volumes. It also mostly reverts a prvious attempt to address this bug:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/170907/

Change-Id: I7682fd014c6403d7652c2ad0f53f3ee24f613c8f
Closes-Bug: 1440762

commit_message:
Require disk and container format on image-create

Currently glanceclient doesn't enforce disk-format or container-format
presence in the command line on image-create when providing image data
(with --file, --location, --copy-from), which means that the POST
request is made with the whole image and error is reported by Glance
API.

This post enforces presence of those arguments when image data is
provided so we can get the error quicker and avoid sending unnecessary
data over the network.

Change-Id: I5914fa9cfef190a028b374005adbf3a804b1b677
Closes-Bug: #1309272

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-08-10 11:03:11.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/vmwareapi/vmops.py', 'nova/tests/unit/virt/vmwareapi/test_driver_api.py', 'nova/tests/unit/virt/vmwareapi/test_vmops.py'], 'message': "vmware: use hostnames instead of IPs to differ computes

Currently value of `my_ip' config option is used as image cache dir
prefix to prevent races between nova-compute instances using the same
datastore.

The common practice making nova-compute (with vmwareapi driver chosen)
HA is to have it run in active/passive mode controlled by Pacemaker.
In that case Pacemaker can move nova-compute instance to another host,
should something happen to the original one, which effectively will
cause change of the IP address - thus, all cached images will
have to be re-downloaded again, despite the fact they are still there
in the datastore and still belong to this particular nova-compute
instance.

Hostname, on the other hand, is a kind of special and up until
recently nova-compute manager would even delete all instances, if the
hostname changed (see #1471887 for details). Thus, when running in
active/passive mode nova-compute often has the same hostname (set
by the means of `host' config option), no matter on which node of
the OpenStack cluster it's currently running.

Change-Id: I6c6a3a8cf9899d8385ccf7e18fbc4702fd9b01fe
"}]
commit_message:
vmware: use hostnames instead of IPs to differ computes

Currently value of `my_ip' config option is used as image cache dir
prefix to prevent races between nova-compute instances using the same
datastore.

The common practice making nova-compute (with vmwareapi driver chosen)
HA is to have it run in active/passive mode controlled by Pacemaker.
In that case Pacemaker can move nova-compute instance to another host,
should something happen to the original one, which effectively will
cause change of the IP address - thus, all cached images will
have to be re-downloaded again, despite the fact they are still there
in the datastore and still belong to this particular nova-compute
instance.

Hostname, on the other hand, is a kind of special and up until
recently nova-compute manager would even delete all instances, if the
hostname changed (see #1471887 for details). Thus, when running in
active/passive mode nova-compute often has the same hostname (set
by the means of `host' config option), no matter on which node of
the OpenStack cluster it's currently running.

Change-Id: I6c6a3a8cf9899d8385ccf7e18fbc4702fd9b01fe

commit_message:
Do not allow to deploy multinode in tests

In tests, by default, we create Releases with 'multinode'
mode allowed for clusters, now it is taken from release fixture and
only in places that require it, specific modes for releases are used.

commit_message:
Don't throw ArgumentError from the library

ArgumentError is coupled with the CLI. This patch replaces
it by BadDataError which is more suitable. It also updates
tests and adds tests to cover places where this exception
was not checked.

commit_message:
Add parameter support to pagination-list

Before categories.list did not support passing any parameters to API
call. This commit allows passing parameters, that would be urlencoded
and appended to the url.
This would allow to paginate the query.

Co-Authored-By: Kirill Zaitsev <kzaitsev@mirantis.com>
Change-Id: I9b90624ee5698baa598b18b16400e193fc9c5a1f
Related-bug: #1474932

commit_message:
Add LBaaS unit tests and validations

Unit tests never existed for LBaaS in the Juno plugin, so adding them
in this patch.  This also exposed key validations missing in the
plugin, so they were also added.

This patch is going directly to the stable branch for the following
reasons:

 * All the validations added in this patch already exist in master
 * LBaaS implementation changed significantly between Juno and Kilo for
the MidoNet plugin so it is impossible to cherry-pick.

Change-Id: If2c83b69f1636e0f726fbe4a1f2dbf19216f027a
Fixes: MNP-179

commit_message:
Disallow disabling plugins which roles are used

This achieved by adding a new restriction for plugin-provided
roles which prevents plugin to be disabled if env contains

commit_message:
Define migration states and transitions and use when changing status

We use the newly defined nova/states.py classes to define
of the migration states and their transitions. The idea behind this is
to explicitly define the states and valid transitions for a single
migration object, before we start adding them as a way to track
live-migration/evacuate operations.

This commit also adds a change_status method on the Migration object that
will use the defined state machine to do state transitions (and fail for
invalid ones).

Finally this commit changes all the places that would change the state
to use the change_status() method.

Related-blueprint: migration-fix-resource-tracking
Related-blueprint: robustify-evacuate

Change-Id: I67401df495d2b0df421d0e77f1467d23a30e8b62

commit_message:
Update from global requirements

stable/juno was just created for taskflow from the 0.6.1 tag so that we
can cap networkx (and other requirements) for taskflow in Juno.  This is
needed to unblock the gate-cinder-python26 job in Juno which uses
taskflow and with uncapped networkx, pulls in 1.10 which dropped py26
support.

As the first change to stable/juno for taskflow, this also updates
the .gitreview file.

Depends-On: I29aa97b542d82aabe770ad4431125ef5c67f6104

Closes-Bug: #1484267

Change-Id: Ie5fadc3f26b6897440023b2fdb47a07766061cbb

commit_message:
Improve the efficiency of volume index

As it stands right now, when retrieving the volume without limit, Cinder
will get all volume information from db first. Then get the max limit from
CONF and filter it.
It will waste a lot of memory to do this if there are mass volumes information
in db. So a better way is to get volume directly from db with default limit
and offset if there is no limit passed in.

Here is some of the test data:

Env: There are 60,000 volumes items, 370,000 volume_metadata items and
240,000 volume_glance_metadata items in cinder db.

Old volume index will use nearly 10G memory.
The new volume index will just use about 500M memory.

Change-Id: I1423c574a820a54d5bd7a5468f98ac5092c5f40e
Closes-bug:#1483165

commit_message:
Return HTTP error if network config data is invalid

Previously, PUT /clusters/<cluster_id>/network_configuration/<provider>/
API returned HTTP 200 even if data validation task finished with an error.
This resulted in fuelclient failing to detect an error during network
configuration upload.

Changed this behaviour to return HTTP 400 with a description of the error.

Change-Id: Iafd10c2a1c34390a9b4ee9583bb8f16d2442ed9d
Closes-Bug: #1472662
Closes-Bug: #1469331

commit_message:
Magnum install from source incorrectly places config

The magnum base Dockerfile is placing magnum.conf in
/etc/magnum/magnum/magnum.conf. It should be in
/etc/magnum/magnum.conf.  We need to still cp everything
in that directory because there is more than just the config.

commit_message:
Return HTTP error if network config data is invalid

Previously, PUT /clusters/<cluster_id>/network_configuration/<provider>/
API returned HTTP 200 even if data validation task finished with an error.
This resulted in fuelclient failing to detect an error during network
configuration upload.

Changed this behaviour to return HTTP 400 with a description of the error.

Change-Id: I49ee00a6e11b39e74bcbb8ba6db4861d3c7ac74d
Closes-Bug: #1472662
Closes-Bug: #1469331

commit_message:
Move update code from image create command

Openstack image create command updates existing image (with same name) by
default. That might be confusing since glance allows create multiple
images with same names and may lead to unwanted image update by image
create command.

Image update code was moved from image create action to image set action.

BackwardsIncompatibleImpact

Change-Id: I1686c6544c366262efab9e33c066d5f8a667f707
Closes-Bug: #1461817

commit_message:
libvirt: ensure LibvirtConfigGuestDisk parses readonly/shareable flags

The LibvirtConfigGuestDisk class did not handle parsing of the
readonly flag and was missing support for the shareable flag
entirely. Add support for dealing with both.

Related-bug: #1429220
Change-Id: I69df232951c99f6c79f2c2c0ee95327ca872624e

commit_message:
Listen only for answers to a host

Without this change listener could catch any DISCOVER-OFFER
communication. Even if it is between two another servers.
This may lead to false negativce.

Now listener will only catch answers sent to its requests.

Change-Id: I70821de6f7ffab441bd4cab4d8ec3ccb1351c10b
Closes-bug: #1463935

commit_message:
Cinder_volumes_containers are automatically tagged with is_metal

In env.d/cinder.yml there is is_metal:true. 
But there was no mention of it in the documentation.
Therefore, if an user wants to use a cinder volume container with 
netapp/ceph/whatever, the container will be (by default) 
considered as metal.
This should be documented somewhere.

Change-Id: I65e9d0654d50d8c8825f858e89fdf4595134dddb

Use a workaround to make lb_policy work

'project' and 'trust' field can not be defined in RequestContext
at the same time. However, 'project' field is needed for building
DB session. Therefore, before we rework context related design,
we temporarily use a workaround to make lb_policy work.

commit_message:
Remove "tenants" from user_attribute_ignore default

It doesn't matter if "tenants" is ignored or not since keystone doesn't
use it. Remove it from the default for user_attribute_ignore since an
admin might think it's actually used for something.

Change-Id: I000d895a88887dff71076e79fcd6e96947a44b86

subject: Update LoadBalancer with signal, not update
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-10-10 13:59:50.000000000', 'files': ['heat/engine/resources/autoscaling.py', 'heat/tests/test_neutron_autoscaling.py', 'heat/engine/resources/neutron/loadbalancer.py'], 'message': 'Update LoadBalancer with signal, not update

To solve the conflict between a resource update triggered by the
autoscaling group, and a subsequent user initiated update which
will overwrite the members with whatever properties are in the
template, switch to using handle_signal instead:

- Template members are respected as before
- AutoScalingGroups and anything else requiring asynchronous
  addition of members to the LoadBalancer must use resource.signal
- On stack update or resource signal, we combine the two sources
  of members and align the neutron members with both.

Note this has the side-effect of making it possible for instances to
update the loadbalancer if they have stack domain user credentials -
This is possibly a useful in some circumstances but it is an interface
change which affects our security model, so we should probably document
it carefully.

Change-Id: Ibd4f1ba2daf2ffe9375f5b819d17c6ee35a52b97
Closes-Bug: #1379619
'}]
commit_message:
Update LoadBalancer with signal, not update

To solve the conflict between a resource update triggered by the
autoscaling group, and a subsequent user initiated update which
will overwrite the members with whatever properties are in the
template, switch to using handle_signal instead:

- Template members are respected as before
- AutoScalingGroups and anything else requiring asynchronous
  addition of members to the LoadBalancer must use resource.signal
- On stack update or resource signal, we combine the two sources
  of members and align the neutron members with both.

Note this has the side-effect of making it possible for instances to
update the loadbalancer if they have stack domain user credentials -
This is possibly a useful in some circumstances but it is an interface
change which affects our security model, so we should probably document
it carefully.

Change-Id: Ibd4f1ba2daf2ffe9375f5b819d17c6ee35a52b97
Closes-Bug: #1379619

commit_message:
Make sure LDAP filter is constructed correctly

This fixes an issue where, when querying Keystone via the v3 API, you
would get back an invalid LDAP filter, because None was coerced to the
string "None" and inserted into the middle of the query.

Conflicts:
        keystone/tests/unit/common/test_ldap.py

The conflict is due to imports being reorganized in the same area as
this change.

Change-Id: I9d45a4dca265b69e261f134118bb30c8cd128166
Closes-Bug: 1454309
(cherry picked from commit 2c6db4a3bb9e1718744b0e5b03af050fd2866182)

commit_message:
WSGI: make it work, and test it with acceptance

* Finalize httpd service name support in API class following
  puppet-keystone model.
* Implement unit tests.
* Implement separated acceptance tests that deploy Ceilometer API in
  WSGI.

This patch aims to finalize and validate we can deploy Ceilometer API in
WSGI with puppet-ceilometer.
Also that we can update from eventlet to WSGI (it's tested in our beaker jobs).

Closes-bug: #1481532
Change-Id: I3695acf5522457837e079c36d68a0e35dbf6b72c

commit_message:
Do not remove expired revocation events on "get"

Revocation event pruning should only occur on new revocations. This
will limit the volume of churn to the DB/KVS store for revocation
events (and impact to performance).

Change-Id: I1ad7491c54023915c74610287a5095589f12d5c1
Closes-Bug: #1287757
(cherry picked from commit d7e529911c496c71effa1d51e1ecf2399ef359f1)

commit_message:
Scheduler in HA

1) Create new column "processing" in the delayed_calls_v2 table
2) Scheduler takes only objects that marked as processing=false
3) After processing a call scheduler deletes it.

Implements: blueprint scheduler-ha
Change-Id: I465a9c2d7443c352a1cad35f48f5228b64844ded

This modifies how the Pure drivers are determining names for volumes,
snapshots, and consistency group objects. Previously it would rely on
the ‘name’ fields for the Cinder objects, but since this is configurable
and can potentially change it isn’t really very safe…

The new way uses what would be the default values for the names but
forces it to be consistent. This means a user can safely modify the
name template parameter in cinder.conf with a Pure backend and
everything should still work.

This also splits up a little bit of the functionality to make it easier

Closes-Bug: #1483894
'}]
commit_message:
Modify naming helpers in Pure Volume Drivers

This modifies how the Pure drivers are determining names for volumes,
snapshots, and consistency group objects. Previously it would rely on
the ‘name’ fields for the Cinder objects, but since this is configurable
and can potentially change it isn’t really very safe…

The new way uses what would be the default values for the names but
forces it to be consistent. This means a user can safely modify the
name template parameter in cinder.conf with a Pure backend and
everything should still work.

This also splits up a little bit of the functionality to make it easier
to use in future commits.

Change-Id: Ib6c6f1d719dcb9937b6781feb819b101d2398d87
Closes-Bug: #1483894

commit_message:
Add out-of-band RAID configuration support for Cisco Hardware

This blueprint adds support for RAID configuration on Cisco UCS Manager
managed UCS B/C/M-series servers using out-of-band method. UcsSdk
exposes interface for RAID configuration via OOB, this proposal uses
this interface and adds RAID configuration support for UCS drivers.

Change-Id: I73c2c8dafdc6c3d84e4fddaa4a0125146b4b8032

commit_message:
Add a new scheduler for the l3 HA

This patch updates all schedulers in order to support the
scheduling of HA routers. It also refactors and adds tests for
the auto scheduling part.

The schedulers aren't expected to work when creating a router
that's both distributed and highly available. Specific issues
will be reported as bugs and fixed in a future patch.

Partially-implements: blueprint l3-high-availability
Change-Id: I2f80f45adeffa1a4eebcb375a4c8326177e84e83
Co-Authored-By: Assaf Muller <amuller@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Remove redundant statement and refactor

1. Remove redundant pass-statement in except-block.
2. Define "body = None" before if-block to get rid of body-statement both in
   except-block and else-case.
3. Acknowledge error occurred instead of silently squashing it.

Change-Id: I31e17827b40e7a15d88ecacf1fdb2abbbe2da5c0
Signed-off-by: Lin Yang <lin.a.yang@intel.com>

commit_message:
Scaling backup service blueprint spec

Currently the cinder backup service is tightly coupled to the cinder
volume service in ways that prevent scaling out backup services
horizontally across multiple physical nodes.

Here we propose loosening this coupling to enable backup processes
to run on multiple nodes without having to be colocated with volume
services.

Implements: bp scalable-backup-service

Change-Id: Ibd56014ca15e058918bacfde8d8a71e7d179dd77

commit_message:
Poll functionality for stack create action

Poll functionality is required for long running stacks.

When stack-create is passed with --poll argument, it will first print
stack-show output and then continously print the events in log format
until stack completes its action with success/failure.

This patch only implements poll for stack create action.

DocImpact
A new option --poll is added to stack-create.

Partial-Bug: #1420541

Change-Id: Ib7d35b66521f0ccca8544fd18fb70e04eaf98e5a

commit_message:
Skip non-doc and test-only jobs for for all branches

There is no much reason to skip it for master but not feature and
stable branches. And it only makes life harder for those stuck with
their features in feature branches.

While at it, expanded the filter to neutron-fullstack job to skip unit
test changes and other changes that are irrelevant for gate without
devstack.

Finally, moved other dsvm filters under more wide filter common to all
projects.

Change-Id: I4954a2aa7b2ede85843ccd51686bf648dd3782c6

commit_message:
py34: test_hot and test_validate

* use hashlib.algorithms_available in PY3 and hashlib.algorithms in PY2
* use e.args[0] instead of six.text_type(e) which will otherwise
  result in the unicode literal being flattened.
* add stubs to prevent actual API calls in tests.
* constraint the test template to help in more accurate testing which
  otherwise results in iterating through other unnecessary items.

partial blueprint heat-python34-support

Change-Id: I7480555330161cf6f197c83f3245685511284307

commit_message:
Update snap-quota to unlimited in Nimble driver

Change the snap-quota from limited fix size of the volume
to unlimited on the Nimble driver. This applies to creating
a new volume, extending an existing volume and creating a
clone from an existing volume snapshot.

Change-Id: Id22836559554c10074c1a14d837a09dbe01b52f8
Closes-Bug: #1463214

commit_message:
networking-tricircle core plugin and security group

Initial implementation include option to use ML2 but it seem that it
will be better to use a core plugin (more control) over the process.

This just includes the Neutron side plugin. It replaces the ML2 plugin
with one that doesn't do any actual network changes, instead only
forwards it to the Cascade Service.

Change-Id: Ic63e7a3d0a1b171d43aff535b65c949e9e51ff4f

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-08-13 21:17:43.000000000', 'files': ['heat/engine/service_software_config.py', 'heat/tests/engine/test_software_config.py', 'heat/common/exception.py'], 'message': 'Use atomic_key for deployment metadata updates

This change switches _push_metadata_software_deployments over to
using db_api.resource_update for deployment resource metadata
updates.

Using the atomic_key filter of resource_update allows this code
to detect if another transaction has updated the metadata, and
the wrap_db_retry decorator is used to perform retry attempts. No actual
resource locking is required since we just need to detect if another
transaction performed an update, so the engine_id is not specified.

This change uses db_api directly rather than the Resource object since
this change will need to be backported to Kilo (db_api.resource_update
was created for convergence, and is in Kilo, but Resource object using
it is not). This change can switch back to using the Resource object once the
backport is complete.

This rows_updated/RetryRequest/wrap_db_retry technique is used by other
OpenStack projects for concurrent transaction detection (such as nova,
for floating IP allocation).

Change-Id: Ibf9dd58a66a77d9ae9d4b519b0f11567977f416c
Closes-Bug: #1477329
'}]
commit_message:
Use atomic_key for deployment metadata updates

This change switches _push_metadata_software_deployments over to
using db_api.resource_update for deployment resource metadata
updates.

Using the atomic_key filter of resource_update allows this code
to detect if another transaction has updated the metadata, and
the wrap_db_retry decorator is used to perform retry attempts. No actual
resource locking is required since we just need to detect if another
transaction performed an update, so the engine_id is not specified.

This change uses db_api directly rather than the Resource object since
this change will need to be backported to Kilo (db_api.resource_update
was created for convergence, and is in Kilo, but Resource object using
it is not). This change can switch back to using the Resource object once the
backport is complete.

This rows_updated/RetryRequest/wrap_db_retry technique is used by other
OpenStack projects for concurrent transaction detection (such as nova,
for floating IP allocation).

Change-Id: Ibf9dd58a66a77d9ae9d4b519b0f11567977f416c
Closes-Bug: #1477329

commit_message:
Move DIB components to support depends-on

Until support for zuul-cloner arrives for bifrost's CI settings,
we need mechanisms to allow us test against a dependent revision
in the diskimage-builder repositioy.

As such, we've moved the diskimage-builder download and installation
to align with the other packages from source, and updated the CI
prep role to apply dependent revisions.

Additionally, correct conditionals in the OpenStack CI prep role.

Change-Id: Ie5db11ff7d2160c7cea9a71aebd86d1b369983c1

commit_message:
Remove the group_vars/all file for easy customization

Removal and split of the group_vars all file resulted in a general
clean-up and optomization of dependency information with-in the
roles as defaults are required and a number of them were being
supplied from group_vars/all.

Additionally split out the group_vars/all file into
group_vars/baremetal and group_vars/localhost files with
improved comments to help direct a user wanting to perform
deeper customization.

Due to variable loading processes, additionally unwire the bifrost-
create-bootable-image role, as it is no longer developed upon and
the default vars are conflicting with the variables used across
role.

Additionally updated READMEs where appropriate.

Co-Authored-By: stephane <stephane@alum.mit.edu>
Change-Id: Ia6226a8573753ff02da19dcb3c2b5abfb9b3c297

commit_message:
db_base_plugin_v2: Avoid creating another session

Instead of get_admin_context(), use context.elevated() to avoid
creating another DB session.

get_admin_context().session creates an independent DB session,
while ctx.elevated().session shares the original context's session.
Generally it's better to avoid using multiple DB sessions in
a single thread as it's a bad idea for various reasons:
- They can yield inconsistent views
- They can ends up with a deadlock

Change-Id: I5ef54cbabab552bad28a147254372b0cdc022832

commit_message:
Fix update_subnet for prefix delegation

A misnamed function call and execution order issue was causing
update_subnet to fail when a PD enabled subnet received a new CIDR.

This patch fixes the issues, and introduces an rpc api test to
ensure the function works. This includes altering the process_prefix_update
RPC handler to expose the issue to the test.

Change-Id: Id1e781291f711865fd783ed5e0208694097b7024
Closes-Bug: 1482676

commit_message:
Support for independent alembic branches in sub-projects

Sub-projects shall now register their independent alembic migrations
via entrypoints in setup.cfg, and neutron-db-manage will discover them
and run them automatically.

If a service or sub-project is specified explicitly, then
neutron-db-manage will run on only that service or sub-project.

The advanced services project are just special cases of sub-projects.
For example, specifying the CLI option '--service lbaas' is the same
as specifying '--subproject neutron-lbaas'.

Specifying no service or sub-project will cause neutron-db-manage to
run the command on neutron and all installed sub-projects.

Added and consolidated documentation into devref for alembic migrations.

Partial-Bug: #1471333
Partial-Bug: #1470625

Change-Id: I9a06de64ce35675af28adf819de6f22dc832390d

mechanism_driver is no longer valid. The new entry point is defined in
the networking-bigswitch stackforge repo.

Fix for Logical Switch not getting deleted

The logical switch table has to be deleted when the
last switch from the ovsdb is deleted. This patch
implements the same.

Closes-Bug:1453097

commit_message:
Create a Bootstrap Theme Preview Page with HTML Hints

Themers need an easy way to see how customizations in
the new themeing mechanism will affect known bootstrap
elements.

While debug mode is true, the currently loaded theme
and boostrap markup hints will be available at
http://{host:port}/skin.

Makes use of and adapts the Bootstrap preview html snippet:
http://codepen.io/jamesabels/pen/FvhsG
and Bootswatch's html hints.

Change-Id: I167c1b324fd0affcce31926abda3f3b00a37e1fd
Implements: blueprint bootstrap-theme-preview

subject: Don't import files with backed files
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-08-13 18:48:14.000000000', 'files': ['glance/tests/unit/async/flows/test_import.py', 'glance/async/flows/base_import.py'], 'message': "Don't import files with backed files

There's a security issue where it'd be possible to import images with
backed files using the task engine and then use/convert those to access
system files or any other file in the system. An example of an attack
would be to import an image with a backing file pointing to
`/etc/passwd`, then convert it to raw and download the generated image.

This patch forbids importing files with baking files entirely. It does
that in the `_ImportToFS` task, which is the one that imports the image
locally to then execute other tasks on it. It's not necessary for the
`_ImportToStore` task because other tasks won't be executed when the
image is imported in the final store.

Change-Id: I35f43c3b3f326942fb53b7dadb94700ac4513494
Closes-bug: #1471912
"}]
commit_message:
Don't import files with backed files

There's a security issue where it'd be possible to import images with
backed files using the task engine and then use/convert those to access
system files or any other file in the system. An example of an attack
would be to import an image with a backing file pointing to
`/etc/passwd`, then convert it to raw and download the generated image.

This patch forbids importing files with baking files entirely. It does
that in the `_ImportToFS` task, which is the one that imports the image
locally to then execute other tasks on it. It's not necessary for the
`_ImportToStore` task because other tasks won't be executed when the
image is imported in the final store.

commit_message:
Support host type specific block volume attachment

----
NOTE(markus_z): Nova uses os-brick since commit
e6cdd1693ba843e1c8dcccbde3af20f62eb0b5a2. That's the reason why I
cannot backport a valid nova patch from master. There is an abandoned
change with commit 7357f9691123f7736b60bf2b4a86b479c974bdc7 which
contains the needed change, but that would cause confusion.

os-brick contains this change with commit
b1a8c2e1f18d424adfdfa29bae47cafa4700dcee which is marked as
implementing a blueprint, but should have been a bug in the first
place.
----

Add the platform and operating system type to the connector to allow a
Cinder driver to set host type specific configuration attributes when
attaching a Fibre-Channel volume.

Closes-Bug: #1471810

Change-Id: I74bdc527f94b5f4eefd4341d0bf9aa754a8a140b

"Delete VIP" is not a batch action so it makes sense to use
tables.Action instead of tables.DeleteAction to prevent extra
success message which is in fact incorrect. "Delete VIP" is
a specific action: there is no separate tab for VIPs. That's
why pool's id is used for this message. Moreover, a default
confirmation message is quite confusing too: "You have selected
<pool name associated with VIP>". This patch adds a custom help
text with VIP id to this message.

'}]
commit_message:
Delete VIP action refactoring

"Delete VIP" is not a batch action so it makes sense to use
tables.Action instead of tables.DeleteAction to prevent extra
success message which is in fact incorrect. "Delete VIP" is
a specific action: there is no separate tab for VIPs. That's
why pool's id is used for this message. Moreover, a default
confirmation message is quite confusing too: "You have selected
<pool name associated with VIP>". This patch adds a custom help
text with VIP id to this message.

Closes-Bug: #1439180

Change-Id: I74c13bcbee56e22d8814e8a4118c906c23e2405e

commit_message:

Remove the specification in tox.ini that _ is a builtin so that
it will no longer assume that _ does not need to be imported.
This helps ensure that the _ from i18n is used.

Activating this check did not flag any violations.

commit_message:
All the Cinder services need to reference the correct config

Every service except cinder-api was looking for the file
'/opt/kolla/cinder/cinder-<service>.conf' when the config file in place was named
'cinder.conf'.  Change the rest of the services to look for cinder.conf or
the config file will never be copied over to into '/etc/cinder/'.

Change-Id: I1cd59f1da09e6f3bc7e7b3a4f45f9da2b8247479
Closes-Bug: #1481928
Closes-Bug: #1484248

commit_message:
Validate tenant_id between firewall and firewall-policy

This change ensures that on firewall create/update, the
firewall-policy (if provided) is shared, or belongs to firewall tenant.

revisions:
[{'number': 6, 'created': '2015-08-05 04:52:00.000000000', 'files': ['nova/compute/resource_tracker.py'], 'message': "Update hypervisor stats in booting failed case

As a periodic activity, available resources for compute node are
updated using instances db to maintain a collective view of
available resources at hypervisor level. 'nova hypervisor-stats' is
expected to show this view of resources. Currently resources are
updated from all instances available in db except the ones that have
vm_state as 'deleted'. In booting failed case, resources are released
and process is aborted but soon after this when periodic updation of
available resources for the corresponding compute happens, again
already released resouces for errored VM gets considered. To fix this
long with deleted, VMs in error state should also be skipped.

Change-Id: I9b51596bc11dbb32b2ca561d7dfc280f7f5277e5
Closes-Bug: #1446449
"}]
commit_message:
Update hypervisor stats in booting failed case

As a periodic activity, available resources for compute node are
updated using instances db to maintain a collective view of
available resources at hypervisor level. 'nova hypervisor-stats' is
expected to show this view of resources. Currently resources are
updated from all instances available in db except the ones that have
vm_state as 'deleted'. In booting failed case, resources are released
and process is aborted but soon after this when periodic updation of
available resources for the corresponding compute happens, again
already released resouces for errored VM gets considered. To fix this
long with deleted, VMs in error state should also be skipped.

Change-Id: I9b51596bc11dbb32b2ca561d7dfc280f7f5277e5
Closes-Bug: #1446449

commit_message:
Add Request ID to outbound calls when set

When a request is made with X-OpenStack-Request-ID headers set then this
value should be included in the headers of calls that this service makes
so that the effects of a call can be traced throughout a cloud.

Include this header in any requests made with the plugin.

At this time I haven't included trying to create a request ID if one is
not present. This is probably something that auth_token middleware
should own.

Implements: bp request-helpers
Change-Id: Ia4137f68bcb3b13a32c8e54d2fdd63f4e0fd6944

commit_message:
Fetch resource ID as unicode

When coming from the command line resource get requests come through as
ascii encoded strings even when they are unicode. By always converting
this to unicode we allow requests to handle the ascii conversion
components of the request we prevent string manipulation that happens in
session from throwing UnicodeDecodeErrors.

Change-Id: I9ab643941eb0b596f2b717d7ab6ba6c1a5a30288
Closes-Bug: #1465500

commit_message:
Use the Glance Data container for ansible

Ansible doesn't use the Glance data container rather it mounts
the volumes into the API container and puts it to sleep.  Instead,
use the data container and put it to sleep.

Partially-implements: blueprint ansible-data-containers

commit_message:
Fix timestamp comparison in alarm state history

Fixes JAH-1923.
Fixes 'alarms state history "offset" behavior same as "limit"'.

Make Monasca-API alarm state history resource use time format 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS'
in String type for offset comparisons.

For some reason the particular queries in alarm state history do not work with Timestamp type.
This could be a bug or inconsistency in Vertica.

The other Timestamp camparisons in other resources seem to work as expected. Tested measurement-list
and all time comparisons are working there.

Change-Id: Ic7a4f8b596164de6f19f02a2529a7c86bdcf61b7

commit_message:
Acknowledgements implementation

In order to make zmq driver implementation reliable
support acknowledgements receiving from server side.
Acknowledgements feature is supported only by
DEALER/ROUTER publisher/consumer pair because other
socket types don't support back-chatter.

More pluggable publishers/consumers added (PUSH/PULL).

Change-Id: I0d02394561c895575045668b43b4b7946f3a8239

This patch does the following:

1. Introduces two new Keystone variables which are useful for
   debugging the Keystone service. The values are defaulted

   - keystone_wsgi_processes: number of wsgi processes to run
   - keystone_wsgi_threads: number of wsgi threads to run

4. Moves the keystone service and admin processes into their
   own wsgi groups for better isolation.

5. Sets each wsgi process to run under the keystone group.

6. Bring the configuration file in line with the upstream
   recommended configuration as at 4 Aug 2015 in order to
   overcome import race conditions.

Change-Id: I861d1ef233dd6121452dc0e9e590d2d9f9b7973e

(cherry picked from commit 98c9768497145e03d349f6ddee8dc89b4bda13f9)

commit_message:
Improve Keystone Apache configuration

This patch does the following:

1. Introduces two new Keystone variables which are useful for
   debugging the Keystone service. The values are defaulted
   to the same values as before the patch.
   - keystone_wsgi_processes: number of wsgi processes to run
   - keystone_wsgi_threads: number of wsgi threads to run

4. Moves the keystone service and admin processes into their
   own wsgi groups for better isolation.

5. Sets each wsgi process to run under the keystone group.

6. Bring the configuration file in line with the upstream
   recommended configuration as at 4 Aug 2015 in order to
   overcome import race conditions.

Change-Id: I861d1ef233dd6121452dc0e9e590d2d9f9b7973e
Closes-Bug: #1481339
(cherry picked from commit 98c9768497145e03d349f6ddee8dc89b4bda13f9)

commit_message:
pci: Remove get_pci_devices_filter() method

Continuing the cleanup of the PCI modules, this patch gets rid of the
nova.pci.whitelist.get_pci_devices_filter() method which did nothing
other than return a nova.pci.whitelist.PciHostDevicesWhiteList object.
While at it, rename the PciHostDevicesWhiteList class to just Whitelist
to save eyeballs.

Change-Id: I403248c5343d5ac97d9ab7716e2c817fcc30a3b7

commit_message:
Don't run gate-neutron-vpnaas-dsvm-functional-sswan on stable/juno

The strongswan support was not in vpnaas in Juno so the job won't work
(devstack doesn't set it up in stable/juno).

The neutron-vpnaas repo has a stable/juno branch but it's not used so
this hasn't been a problem so far.  And neutron runs the sswan job in
the experiemental queue, so while it would fail there in stable/juno,
it's the experimental queue so it's not blocking.

This cleans things up though to avoid confusion.

Change-Id: I75c097d0d1f811e1ba8673b0003f8a5790d23a69

commit_message:
Raise the cap on kombu to 3.0.15 since that's when kombu supports py34

taskflow on stable/juno fails py34 testing since kombu 3.0.7 does not
support python 3.4.  We have to fix taskflow on stable/juno to release
0.6.2 with capped networkx so that cinder py26 tests pass again.

So this is needed for Ie5fadc3f26b6897440023b2fdb47a07766061cbb to pass
tests.

Note that kombu is uncapped in stable/kilo g-r.  I'm not totally sure if
kombu needs to be capped at all in stable/juno, but it seems safer to
raise the cap rather than remove it.

Partial-Bug: #1484267

Change-Id: I29aa97b542d82aabe770ad4431125ef5c67f6104

commit_message:
Use playbook status to report upgrade failure

Previously, we simply checked $? which at that point would be the exit
status of echo, not openstack-ansible. By recording the actual
openstack-ansible exit status, we can properly report failures of the
upgrade script.

Closes-bug: 1480342
Change-Id: Icf43bea84660e4160a2dfcdb4ac93055340b3573
(cherry picked from commit 8a106d184a566f1baed616aee7747d5f2d581c1b)

commit_message:
Add swift service region to group vars

The swift service region is currently only set in the swift playbook
defaults file. It needs to be exposed in group vars and controlled by
the global `service_region` variable.

Closes-Bug: #1481700

commit_message:
move supported-boot-device-list spec (1 of 2)

spec needs to live in the approved/, not the liberty/,
subdirectory. (With a placeholder in the old directory.)
This move will be done in two commits to preserve the history;
git can't recognize a rename and replace operation in the same commit.

commit_message:
Remove project_id from db.add_item interface

Since there is no part of code which adds an db item with other project,
this backdoor is not needed.

This patch removes this argument and its proxying by util functions.

This reverts commit b51eb4f35028d4861d4fc7df5eb9dc39b29c26e7.

commit_message:
Use id mapping for auto creation of db item for alien images

In according to initial DB API contract, a user can not modify db items
of other project. Shortly before 0.1.0 release this had been broken due
to a critical bugfix.

This patch makes images to avoid creating of db item in other project.
It uses db mapping instead.

Change-Id: I07119b7e1348bbe63e5c736dad4141daa2a07fb9

commit_message:
Use id mapping in get_os_image

A public alien image can has id mapping only, but not a regular db item.
This leads to unexpected InvalidAMIID.NotFound error on certain
requests. An added test checks one such case.

Change-Id: Ie6fd0f877cbf4bdcf8b44cec82dc9cc8fb24918a

subject: Don't import files with backed files
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-08-13 18:59:15.000000000', 'files': ['glance/tests/unit/async/flows/test_import.py', 'glance/async/flows/base_import.py'], 'message': "Don't import files with backed files

There's a security issue where it'd be possible to import images with
backed files using the task engine and then use/convert those to access
system files or any other file in the system. An example of an attack
would be to import an image with a backing file pointing to
`/etc/passwd`, then convert it to raw and download the generated image.

This patch forbids importing files with baking files entirely. It does
that in the `_ImportToFS` task, which is the one that imports the image
locally to then execute other tasks on it. It's not necessary for the
`_ImportToStore` task because other tasks won't be executed when the
image is imported in the final store.

Change-Id: I35f43c3b3f326942fb53b7dadb94700ac4513494
Closes-bug: #1471912
(cherry picked from commit d529863a1e8d2307526bdb395b4aebe97f81603d)
"}]
commit_message:
Don't import files with backed files

There's a security issue where it'd be possible to import images with
backed files using the task engine and then use/convert those to access
system files or any other file in the system. An example of an attack
would be to import an image with a backing file pointing to
`/etc/passwd`, then convert it to raw and download the generated image.

This patch forbids importing files with baking files entirely. It does
that in the `_ImportToFS` task, which is the one that imports the image
locally to then execute other tasks on it. It's not necessary for the
`_ImportToStore` task because other tasks won't be executed when the
image is imported in the final store.

Change-Id: I35f43c3b3f326942fb53b7dadb94700ac4513494
Closes-bug: #1471912
(cherry picked from commit d529863a1e8d2307526bdb395b4aebe97f81603d)

commit_message:
Do not make delete_db_firewall conditional

The delete_db_firewall should not be made conditional, as the
ability to delete the firewall is already determined by the caller.

This patch improves debug statements to ease troubleshooting.

Related-bug: #1483875

Change-Id: I35b171e5827af9b6217605c0654386704f4fab83

commit_message:
Inherit RequestContext from oslo_context's RequestContext

Before murano used RequestContext, inherited from object.
oslo_context has graduated and includes a bunch of features, that is
used by oslo_log and other oslo modules.
In particular this commit enables logging of request_id, user_id and
tenant_id in all context-aware requests.
Alters tests tto make them pass regardless of the new context.

Targets blueprint: murano-x-openstack-request-id-support

Change-Id: Ic22f67ae89881581254de8787fa3632dfa1af08f

commit_message:
Implement Murano source images

* Both api and engine start up without error, but can't test properly
until Horizon is fixed (bug #1482196)

* These are source installs are there no RPMs available for Murano
that I can find.

* Also requires a plugin for horizon that will be made as a
separate commit

Co-Authored-By: Mick Thompson <michael.a.thompson@oracle.com>
Implements: blueprint enable-murano-container

Change-Id: Ia46985b21bb5f6d7690501e7199800c8c7fcb51f

commit_message:
Fix OVN_PORT_BINDING_PROFILE

The conversion to the ml2 plugin broke this integration. This patch fixes it.
It also removes the function _validate_bindign_profile and instead uses
_get_data_from_binding_profile to return the data and validate it this way
we only need to call one method. Lastly, this patch changes the prototypes to
create_port_in_ovn to pass parent_name and tag as these are not in the port
object.

Change-Id: I89a6b732d5bfaf9625276caa6ec3ed51f6bf0416

commit_message:
Revert "Fix logical port delete"

I'm not able to reproduce the behavior that this patchset stated in it's
commit message about ports not being deleted in ovsdb. In addition this
patch is now causing 3 tempest tests to fail which were passing before and
is yielding this trace in the logs.

This reverts commit d78273a8d0dd5f6124a101d0c031c7a868d7220a.

Change-Id: Idc0d27248d5ac02b904babf1cec2fb71ce102101

commit_message:
Don't include encryption algorithm in phase2alg for the AH protocol

AH protocol doesn't have any encryption. That is why phase2alg in
ipsec.conf template should be modified to exclude encryption for AH.
Modified statements in ipsec.template.conf to avoid generation of
whitespaces during rendering.

Also made sure that each test has its own copy of FAKE_VPN_SERVICE
without overriding the original one. Added a helper method for
generating of unified diff to make debugging tests that generate
and compare long outputs (e.g. configs) easier.

Change-Id: Iaefae0c41a1e5a5a09b9882cb345ba44d08d6465
Closes-Bug: #1476681

commit_message:
StrongSwanProcess: redefine DIALECT_MAP at class level

DIALECT_MAP is a class variable of BaseSwanProcess which is a base
class for StrongSwanProcess and OpenSwanProcess. Overwriting class
variables at instance init is not safe and it leads to sideefects,
i.e. when running UTs for both StrongSwanProcess and OpenSwanProcess.

DIALECT_MAP should be instead be redefined in StrongSwanProcess class
namespace.

Change-Id: I705ea4863a14fc6ecf3e0f16142e4f375c75cd62
Closes-Bug: #1477570

IP. As a result, if a connection is established, the user will have no way of
knowing the peer's external IP (no way to query it).

To support this we'll let the service driver determine the public facing

and will store it in the service table. This will be used for every

and/or IPv6 tunnel IPs.

peer's IP version (as is done today).

same IP version as the peer address. A separate commit could add validation
code to make sure that one exists, and if not, reject the IPSec connection.

For database migration, the new field will be populated from the router's
GW IP address(s). Since there is not a grenade job available for VPN

Closes-Bug: 1464387

commit_message:
VPNaaS: Store local side's tunnel IP for later retrieval

In use cases where the VPN functionality is provided outside of the neutron
router (e.g. separate appliance, VM, H/W, external S/W), the local side's
tunnel IP address for IPSec connections will not be the Neutron router's GW
IP. As a result, if a connection is established, the user will have no way of
knowing the peer's external IP (no way to query it).

To support this we'll let the service driver determine the public facing
tunnel IP for this side (called external_ip internally for IPsec drivers),
and will store it in the service table. This will be used for every
connection created for that service (instead of looking up the router's GW IP),
and will be available via the GET API, so that the external IP can be obtained
and then specified by the peer end, when setting up an IPSec connection.

Keep in mind, however, when IPSec connections are created today, they will
select the GW IP based on the IP version of the peer's address. There could
be one connection using a V6 IP and another using a V4 IP.

To handle this, we'll use two entries in the service table to hold IPv4
and/or IPv6 tunnel IPs.

For the existing implementations, the external IP is the router's GW IP, so
the default service driver will store that information (again, IPv4 and/or
IPv6). Each IPSec connection will use the appropriate IP version, based on
peer's IP version (as is done today).

Note: The current code does not make sure there is an external IP with the
same IP version as the peer address. A separate commit could add validation
code to make sure that one exists, and if not, reject the IPSec connection.

For database migration, the new field will be populated from the router's
GW IP address(s). Since there is not a grenade job available for VPN
currently, the migration was tested manually.

Change-Id: I0cdded5105ad8000131e39a86cbfa80ed89ae37b
Closes-Bug: 1464387

The transaction manager enables us to batch together various operations.
It is currently being used in nova-powervm to batch together the storage
mapping operations.

This change set builts on previous ones.  It adds the vOpt media to the
FeedTask (or tx_mgr).  This allows for one less independent mapping on
the spawn action.

Note that this undoes a change that has the network and the storage run
in parallel.  This is because the config drive requires input from the
network.  The overall benefit of putting the config drive in the tx_mgr
far outweighs running the network and storage in parallel.

A future change set will evaluate running all the storage and network
'creates' in parallel.

Change-Id: Ibeaa8f796372f33595650a62237206b396946e62
"}]
commit_message:
Add vOpt media to the FeedTask

The transaction manager enables us to batch together various operations.
It is currently being used in nova-powervm to batch together the storage
mapping operations.

This change set builts on previous ones.  It adds the vOpt media to the
FeedTask (or tx_mgr).  This allows for one less independent mapping on
the spawn action.

Note that this undoes a change that has the network and the storage run
in parallel.  This is because the config drive requires input from the
network.  The overall benefit of putting the config drive in the tx_mgr
far outweighs running the network and storage in parallel.

A future change set will evaluate running all the storage and network
'creates' in parallel.

Change-Id: Ibeaa8f796372f33595650a62237206b396946e62

commit_message:
Fix _update_subnet_allocation_pools returning empty list

_update_subnet_allocation_pools was returning an empty list in all
cases due to trying to iterate over the same generator twice.
Generators cannot be iterated over multiple times.

This patch changes the generator into a list to fix this problem,
and alters the unit test so that this issue is exposed.

Change-Id: Iea98f3ae4f16964cd68154ac5edfeb125de889e0
Closes-Bug: 1483687

commit_message:
libvirt: mark NUMA huge page mappings as shared access

When a guest is configured to use huge page backed memory,
these mappings should be marked as shared. This allows a
external process connected to a vhostuser VIF type to
access the guest RAM segment.

Closes-bug: #1447079
Change-Id: I1136929d921cdb915de6553e6f0f93e7b29b547e

commit_message:
Fix creation of endpoints in multi-region

Keystone API v3 does currently not support filtering for region names.
As a consequence an additional check is needed in get_or_create_endpoint
to check if an endpoint must be created for a given region or if it
already exists.
See related bug for more information regarding the missing region
filtering in keystone.

Closes-Bug: #1483784
Related-Bug: #1482772
Change-Id: Ia6a497b9fb58f7474636ab52dc01b99857bed3a2

commit_message:
Update kilo for new dev work - 10 Aug 2015

Update all repo SHAs for new work on 11.1.1

The python package pbr needs to be capped to <0.11
until https://review.openstack.org/211800 merges
in upstream heat.

Due to a build failure in the required python-openstacksdk
this patch temporarily fixes the version to one that builds
successfully. More information about this in:
 - https://launchpad.net/bugs/1484011

Related-Bug: #1484011
Closes-Bug: #1450733
Change-Id: I415e23f2d4e4f1770ac4a03313b0dd984db8a671

subject: Adds venv environment to tox for -infra docs job
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2015-08-13 09:01:15.000000000', 'files': ['doc/source/index.rst', 'requirements.txt', 'doc/source/_static/.gitkeep', 'tox.ini'], 'message': "Adds venv environment to tox for -infra docs job

The -infra templated job for docs requires that a venv be created using
tox. It will actually run this command to build the documentation:

  tox -evenv -- python setup.py build_sphinx

This patch also switches to using ansible 1.6.10 - it's the same version
as was present in requirements before, but the download will not be from
a Rackspace mirror. This is done to resolve a doc build failure when
the requirement is set using the previous method.

As there are no in-tree docs for the juno branch, this patch adds a bare
index which references the Rackspace documentation.

Change-Id: I69d7e0ab5613487c402f35d3ebb88915a48f50ce
"}]
commit_message:
Adds venv environment to tox for -infra docs job

The -infra templated job for docs requires that a venv be created using
tox. It will actually run this command to build the documentation:

  tox -evenv -- python setup.py build_sphinx

This patch also switches to using ansible 1.6.10 - it's the same version
as was present in requirements before, but the download will not be from
a Rackspace mirror. This is done to resolve a doc build failure when
the requirement is set using the previous method.

As there are no in-tree docs for the juno branch, this patch adds a bare
index which references the Rackspace documentation.

Change-Id: I69d7e0ab5613487c402f35d3ebb88915a48f50ce

commit_message:
Add hacking check for greenthread.spawn()

Because greenthread.spawn() and spawn_n() are missing a nova context
(see I3623e60c49e442e2431cf017540422aa59bc285a and
Ia5175c9729069df3d779237ba6039cf5bc920018), nova.utils.spawn() and
spawn_n() should be used when spawning threads. This change adds a
hacking check to assert this is being done during pep8.

Change-Id: Id52c30bb5ded2184d772e6026b0f04f9a0efeb55
Related-Bug: #1404268
Closes-Bug: #1468513

commit_message:
Adds Debian & derivatives packaging to OpenStack

We would like to have the packaging Git repositories for Debian
hosted in the /openstack namespace.

As per discussions, the RPM folks would be packaging separately, and
we wouldn't form a single team.

Within the projects, the following vendors would be involved:
- Debian contributors
- MOS Linux (for the Debian part of it)
- Maybe H-Linux if they also want to participate

This commit contains an initial list of package repositories. It
is made currently only of server packages. Packages for Oslo
libraries and clients are currently out of scope of this commit,
however they may appear in the near future.

We already have plans to:
- build automatically, with parts of the tooling already designed.
- gate on each commit using standard distribution tools like
piuparts, lintian, adequate and so on.

The core team is partially defined, and composed with at least:
- Thomas Goirand (PTL for this Liberty cycle)
- Igor Yozhikov
- Ivan Udovichenko
- Daniil Trishkin

We may later on include more core reviewer from Mirantis, and this
list isn't exhaustive yet.

(Thomas asked about update of this patch-set)

Change-Id: I73b64c4bc0497a1d42b6308a038daabab258ede8

commit_message:
Prevent writing security repos twice in MapR plugin

Registration of precise and lucid security repos moved
to separate bash script which is executed only in case
of non-prebuilt images. Prebuilt images already contains
this repos.

Change-Id: I9151e1213b0fa75e4c7e8e16839d269d38a3adce
Closes-Bug: #1482237

commit_message:
Add to execution tasks that are provided by user

Tasks provided with flag *--tasks* will be always added to execution.
This patch is necessary to support this behaviour with flags *--start/--end*.

Change-Id: Ic5e95b5160a824fdca210717efa1a3b884d8e373
Partial-Bug: 1470822

commit_message:
Ship the default image schema in the client

Now that we have stable branches for clients, it's easier to keep track
of the current default image's schema in Glance and update it
respectively. This patch adds the current image schema, including the
schema-properties.

One good reason to do this is to be able to react when a running Glance
instance is not around to be introspected. It's really unfortunate that
things like help text can't be rendered when there image schema is not
available in the system.

We could keep the schema in a json file but rather than shipping data
files with glanceclient we can just have it in the python modules.

Conflicts:
	glanceclient/v2/shell.py

Change-Id: I9b8cc1d18d6717ccf991fb8149ab13c06d653ee4
Closes-bug: #1481729
(cherry picked from commit 3949e0e918e2501c4953a7d9beb58511688d84e1)

commit_message:
Logging migrations for particular server if migration failed

Sometimes, test_live_block_migration fails on multinode job
(gate-tempest-dsvm-multinode-full).
http://logs.openstack.org/91/202391/5/check/gate-tempest-dsvm-multinode-full/f838b41/logs/testr_results.html.gz

If live migration is failed, server status become Active from Migrating but
host is not changed. In that case, test_live_block_migration fails for target
host does not match with server host. But from Tempest failure logs, we do not
know whether migration is failed or something else happened.

It will be better for debugging if this tests logs migrations information
for that server if live migration is failed.

Closes-Bug: 1476478

Change-Id: I0f7ba31e44e6d5508483a6552641f59828af20e1

commit_message:
Ensure server unlocking after test_lock_unlock_server

If assertRaises() in test_lock_unlock_server fails for some
reason, the server remains in locked state and cannot be
deleted after execution of test cases.

addCleanup call for server unlocking is added so that in case
of test_lock_unlock_server failure there will be no hanging
servers in the system after tempest run.

Change-Id: Iff336723d8e03814d9361492b1d5856b785f7a4c
Closes-Bug: #1468623

commit_message:
Don't update RT status when set instance to ERROR

nova will set instance status to ERROR then call RT update
after that, it's not needed becaues RT is used to track instance
state and check whether it's new created or deleted.
Update instance to ERROR in DB should be fine.

Change-Id: I550caf55d32931de1dac43862af15323c18a4431
Closes-Bug: 1453170

commit_message:
Grenade plugin using devstack plugin for ceilometer

This is barebones for now, simply doing the upgrade and checking
services are still running. There is no checking of resources.
Being able to easily add those resources checks is part of the
reason for making this change.

The other reason is to explore and resolve conflicts when extracting
an existing integrated project from both devstack and grenade.

Note that grenade's ensure_services_started and _stopped struggles to
work with processes that contain spaces so distinguishing amongst
ceilometer-polling processes with different namespaces is hard, so
we'll just use the older agent names.

Change-Id: If7bb809743ab0c475a1844c79e552d8b6892a18f

commit_message:
libvirt: qemu-img convert should be skipped when migrating

Image conversion is done to migrate the complete qcow2 image.
But, it is unnecessary to merge the backing file.
I have modified so that nova-compute just copy
the file instead of conversion.
It is possible to move the file in case of
a shared storage environment, but nova resize-revert
fails in that case.

Closes-Bug: #1399098
Change-Id: Ic05b48761f09a4711a11bacfc64cbcf39b352e84

commit_message:
L3 Agent support of manual dvr snat add/remove

This patch handles a corner case when the snat
router is moved from one host to another. The issue
is the cached ex_gw_port will have a different
binding:host_id which should trigger snat
creation/deletion by the agent depending on its
host. Make it so

Change-Id: I1782d49b2bfe909654d5e6a1069f449524532479
Partial-bug: #1369721
Co-Authored-By: Ila Palanisamy <ilavajuthy.palanisamy@hp.com>
Co-Authored-By: Ryan Moats <rmoats@us.ibm.com>

commit_message:
Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/feature/qos' into merge-branch

This merge commit introduces QoS feature into Liberty release of
Neutron.

The feature is documented in: doc/source/devref/quality_of_service.rst
included with the merge patch.

It includes:

- QoS API service plugin with QoS policy and QoS bandwidth limit
  (egress) rule support;
- core plugin mechanism to determine supported rule types, with its ML2
  implementation;
- new agent extension manager;
- QoS agent extension with pluggable backend QoS drivers (Open vSwitch
  and SR-IOV support is included).

To extend network and port core resources with qos_policy_id attribute,
a new ML2 extension driver (qos) was introduced that relies on the QoS
core resource extension (the idea is that eventually we'll get a core
resource extension manager that can be directly reused by core plugins).

Agent-server interaction is based on:

- get_device_details() API that is extended with qos_policy_id;
- a new push/pull mechanism that allows agents and servers to
  communicate using oslo.versionedobjects based objects sent on the
  wire.

The merge includes the following types of test coverage:

- unit tests;
- functional tests for OVS agent, QoS agent extension, and low level
  ovs_lib changes;
- API tests to cover port/network qos_policy_id attribute and new QoS
  resources.

The client changes can be found at:

* https://review.openstack.org/189655
* https://review.openstack.org/198277

The team also prepared fullstack test but it needs to wait for client
merge before it can pass in the gate:

* https://review.openstack.org/202492

Gerrit does not show diff for merge changes that did not result in any
conflict, so to facilitate review, rely on the following steps:

- fetch the patch locally
- git fetch origin
- git diff origin/master...

Partially-Implements: blueprint quantum-qos-api
Partially-Implements: blueprint ml2-qos
Partially-Implements: blueprint ml2-qos-ovs-bwlimiting
Partially-Implements: blueprint ml2-sriov-qos-with-bwlimiting
Change-Id: I92916d0e391791187e9a25ff172fb4b3504857b1

commit_message:
Add REPLACE_DEFAULT_REPOS_ONLY_ONCE variable to manage repos list

export REPLACE_DEFAULT_REPOS_ONLY_ONCE=true
 - Along with REPLACE_DEFAULT_REPOS=true , enables replacing default
   repositories only when Fuel admin node has been installed

export REPLACE_DEFAULT_REPOS_ONLY_ONCE=false
 - Along with REPLACE_DEFAULT_REPOS=true , enables replacing default
   repositories only before a new cluster is created by tests.

export REPLACE_DEFAULT_REPOS=false
 - Disables replacing repositories, Nailgun keeps it's defaults.

Change-Id: Ief45650580cdd897bb785f286d850d27baf06adc
Closes-Bug:#1484137

commit_message:
Move the NPIV Mgmt Mapping into FeedTask

This change set builds on the previous speed up work.  The previous code
had the NPIV management unmapping done within a separate action from the
add to the client VM.

This change set modifies the code such that the NPIV mappings on deploy
are all done within a single transaction.

Change-Id: I5bc431b2a2391600f39b65af184cbda34c8795f5

quotas, usages, reservations and metadata. All of these things are
API-dependent. So, add wrappers, that retries request on 'deadlock'
exceptions.
Also, set database config opt "max_pool_size" to '40' instead of having

Closes-Bug: #1483604

commit_message:
Add retries for deadlock-vulnerable DB methods

It is very likely to get 'deadlock' updating common records such as
quotas, usages, reservations and metadata. All of these things are
API-dependent. So, add wrappers, that retries request on 'deadlock'
exceptions.
Also, set database config opt "max_pool_size" to '40' instead of having
default value - '5'. It allows to keep upto 40 SQL connection alive at
once.

Change-Id: Ia6ec09d4617191c51ad95dd6d9f053141ec1c4c4
Closes-Bug: #1483604

commit_message:
Events RBAC needs scoped token

The role based access control of events api needs project-
scoped tokens to process the request. The project information
has to be available in the request header to be able to filter
events based on the project.In addition to the project, the user
information is also mandated as part of this change. The request
fails with a 403 if this information is not available in the
request.

Change-Id: I2a84c7bd820df66ba4f6dbde6cfac81609e4d1f7

Add tests for python-cinderclient

Add tests for cinder volume creation and deletion
by ID and by Name.

Decreased code duplication.
